================================================================================
                     PROJECT TIMELINE DESCRIPTION
================================================================================

The development of LimenServe follows a comprehensive ten-month timeline spanning 
from October 2025 to July 2026, covering the complete academic year.

OCTOBER - DECEMBER 2025 (First Semester) is dedicated to Proposal Drafting. The 
team researches existing literature, drafts the initial project proposal, defines 
project scope, and prepares documentation for the title defense.

JANUARY 2026 marks the start of the Second Semester with Planning and Requirements 
Analysis. The team conducts the Project Proposal and Title Defense, performs on-site 
interviews and data gathering at Limen Auto Parts Center, and completes the 
Requirements Documentation including the Software Requirements Specification (SRS).

FEBRUARY 2026 focuses on System Design. Activities include UI/UX prototyping and 
wireframe creation in Figma, database schema and architecture planning using 
PostgreSQL, and 3D stockroom layout mapping for the spatial visualization module.

FEBRUARY - APRIL 2026 encompasses the Development phase. Starting in February, the 
team develops the User Management Module and Inventory Module with barcode integration. 
March continues with the POS system, Automated Cost Estimation and Quotation, and 
Service Order Management. April completes development with 3D Spatial Visualization, 
Public Customer Portal, and Reporting Dashboard.

APRIL - MAY 2026 is devoted to Testing. Unit and integration testing using Jest and 
Supertest ensure code quality. User Acceptance Testing (UAT) is conducted with Limen 
Auto Parts Center staff to validate real-world usability.

MAY - JUNE 2026 covers the Evaluation phase. ISO 25010 quality assessment is conducted, 
evaluation surveys are distributed and analyzed, and findings are documented.

SEPTEMBER 2025 - JUNE 2026 represents ongoing Manuscript Preparation that runs parallel 
to all other activities throughout the academic year.

JUNE - JULY 2026 concludes the project with Deployment and Final Defense. The system 
is deployed to Vercel, Render, and Supabase. The Final Oral Defense is conducted, 
manuscript review is completed, and user training sessions are held for handover.


================================================================================
                         DETAILED ACTIVITY BREAKDOWN
================================================================================

OCTOBER - DECEMBER 2025: PROPOSAL DRAFTING
------------------------------------------
  - Research related literature and existing systems
  - Draft initial project proposal
  - Define project scope and objectives
  - Prepare preliminary documentation
  - Review and refine proposal with advisers


JANUARY 2026: PLANNING & REQUIREMENTS ANALYSIS
----------------------------------------------
Week 1-2: Project Proposal & Title Defense
  - Finalize project proposal document
  - Prepare and conduct title defense presentation
  - Incorporate panel feedback

Week 2-3: On-site Interview & Data Gathering
  - Conduct interviews with shop owners (Mr. & Mrs. Limen)
  - Observe current workflow and pain points
  - Document physical stockroom layout (2 floors)
  - Gather sample paper records for digitization reference

Week 3-4: Requirements Documentation
  - Create Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
  - Define functional and non-functional requirements
  - Validate requirements with stakeholders


FEBRUARY 2026: SYSTEM DESIGN & INITIAL DEVELOPMENT
---------------------------------------------------
Week 1-2: UI/UX Prototyping & Wireframes
  - Create initial wireframes in Figma
  - Design user interface mockups
  - Plan navigation and user flows
  - Finalize all screen designs
  - Get stakeholder approval on design

Week 1-2: Database Schema & Architecture
  - Design PostgreSQL database schema
  - Define table relationships (inventory, sales, users, services)
  - Plan API endpoints structure

Week 2-3: 3D Stockroom Layout Mapping
  - Measure physical stockroom dimensions
  - Create 3D model coordinates
  - Plan shelf and item placement system

Week 3-4: User Management Module
  - Implement role-based access control (Admin, Cashier, Stock Clerk)
  - Set up Supabase authentication
  - Create user CRUD operations

Week 3-4: Inventory Module Development Begins
  - Build inventory listing and search
  - Implement barcode scanning integration


MARCH 2026: CORE DEVELOPMENT
----------------------------
Week 1-2: Complete Inventory Module
  - Create low-stock alert system
  - Develop batch entry functionality

Week 1-3: POS & Receipt Printing
  - Set up transaction processing logic
  - Design checkout interface
  - Integrate thermal receipt printer
  - Test payment recording

Week 2-3: Cost Estimation & Quotation Module
  - Build quote calculation engine
  - Create printable quotation templates
  - Implement save/retrieve quotations

Week 3-4: Service Order Management
  - Develop service order tracking
  - Create status workflow (pending → in-progress → complete)
  - Build service history records


APRIL 2026: FEATURE COMPLETION & TESTING BEGINS
-----------------------------------------------
Week 1-2: 3D Spatial Visualization
  - Implement Three.js 3D viewer
  - Create interactive stockroom navigation
  - Link inventory items to 3D positions

Week 2-3: Public Customer Portal
  - Build public inventory browsing
  - Create self-service quotation tool
  - Ensure read-only access restrictions

Week 2-3: Reporting Dashboard
  - Develop sales reports (daily/weekly/monthly)
  - Create inventory movement charts
  - Build service revenue tracking

Week 3-4: Testing Phase Begins
  - Execute unit tests with Jest
  - Run API tests with Supertest
  - Begin User Acceptance Testing with staff


MAY 2026: TESTING & EVALUATION BEGINS
-------------------------------------
Week 1-2: Complete Testing
  - Finalize User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
  - Perform end-to-end tests with Cypress
  - Document and fix identified issues

Week 2-4: Evaluation Begins
  - Begin ISO 25010 quality assessment
  - Prepare evaluation surveys
  - Start collecting user feedback


JUNE 2026: EVALUATION & DEPLOYMENT
----------------------------------
Week 1-2: Complete Evaluation
  - Finalize ISO 25010 quality assessment
  - Distribute and analyze evaluation surveys
  - Compile evaluation results

Week 2-3: Deployment
  - Deploy frontend to Vercel
  - Deploy backend API to Render
  - Deploy database to Supabase

Week 3-4: Final Oral Defense & Manuscript Review
  - Conduct final oral defense presentation
  - Submit manuscript for review
  - Incorporate reviewer feedback


JULY 2026: HANDOVER & COMPLETION
--------------------------------
Week 1-2: Manuscript Finalization
  - Complete manuscript revisions
  - Submit final documentation

Week 2-3: User Training & Handover
  - Conduct training sessions with staff
  - Prepare user manuals and guides
  - Complete system handover to client

Week 4: Project Closure
  - Final documentation submission
  - Project completion sign-off


